The paper deals with the problem of computing the boxicity of graphs, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of parameterized and approximation algorithms suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), and graph theory (cs.GT).
